section.prompt:
Given this product outcome, return: 1. exactly one leading indicator (metric readable weekly, with current/target and a one-line mechanism linking it to the outcome). 2. 2-4 candidate experiments. For each experiment include: name, hypothesis (if X then Y% of users Z), sample_size_estimate, success_criteria, confidence (High | Medium | Low | Exploring).
Outcome: {{outcome_json}}
Rules: - Sample >= 1000 must specify statistical significance at p<0.05. - Sample < 1000 must specify a practical-significance threshold (absolute or relative metric movement). - Success criteria are pre-registered and falsifiable. - At most one experiment may carry High confidence.
